        <div class="bom-journal__downloads">

          <h3 class="bom-journal__subhead">How to Set It Up</h3>
          <p class="bom-journal__small">
             To make this journal, you will need a church account (or access to one) which is easy enough to make. You might need to talk to your bishop or one of his counselors for help getting all the information to make one.

            Use the guide below to learn how to create and use your <strong>notebook</strong> in the <strong>Gospel Living app</strong>.
          </p>

          <a class="bom-journal__download" href="/files/Moroni-Quest-Journal.pdf" target="_blank">
            üìÑ View Journal Setup Slides (PDF)
          </a>
          <!-- Desktop Steps -->
          <h3 class="bom-journal__subhead">Desktop Instructions - Click images to expand</h3>
          <ol class="setup-steps">
            <li class="setup-step">
              <span class="step-num">1</span>
              <div class="step-content">
                <strong>
                  Sign in at
                  <a href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">churchofjesuschrist.org</a>
                </strong>
                <p>After logging in head over to the <strong>Scriptures</strong> (Library menu) in the top left corner (as pictured here)</p>
              </div>
              
              <div class="step-thumbs" aria-label="Step 1 screenshots">
                <button type="button" class="step-thumb" data-full="/img/journal/Picture1.png" data-alt="Scriptures menu">
                  <img src="/img/journal/Picture1.png" alt="Scriptures menu thumbnail" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
                </button>
              </div>
            </li>

            <li class="setup-step">
              <span class="step-num">2</span>
              <div class="step-content">
                <strong>Open Notes</strong>
                <p>In the Scripture Library, a little book icon will appear. Upon clicking it, you will be redirected to your notes.</p>
              </div>
              
              <div class="step-thumbs" aria-label="Step 2 screenshots">
                <button type="button" class="step-thumb" data-full="/img/journal/Picture2.png" data-alt="Notebook Icon ">
                  <img src="/img/journal/Picture2.png" alt="Notebook icon thumbnail" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
                </button>
              </div>
            </li>

            <li class="setup-step">
              <span class="step-num">3</span>
              <div class="step-content">
                <strong>Go to Notebooks</strong>
                <p>While your notes may look different, the ‚ÄúNotebook‚Äù icon on the right will be the exact same. Here is where we will make our very own journal for this journey!</p>
              </div>
              <div class="step-thumbs" aria-label="Step 3 screenshots">
                <button type="button" class="step-thumb" data-full="/img/journal/Picture3.png" data-alt="Notebooks">
                  <img src="/img/journal/Picture3.png" alt="Notebooks thumbnail" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
                </button>
              </div>
            </li>

            <li class="setup-step">
              <span class="step-num">4</span>
              <div class="step-content">
                <strong>Create your ‚ÄúMoroni‚Äôs Quest‚Äù notebook</strong>
                <p>Once here, all you need to do is create your very own journal by clicking the <strong>Create Notebook</strong> and titling it something to remember. I chose ‚ÄúMoroni‚Äôs Quest‚Äù but you can choose any title. You‚Äôre ready to write your first entry! Spend some time here learning to add new entries.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="step-thumbs" aria-label="Step 4 screenshots">
                <button type="button" class="step-thumb" data-full="/img/journal/Picture4.png" data-alt="Create notebook">
                  <img src="/img/journal/Picture4.png" alt="Create notebook thumbnail" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
                </button>

                <div class="step-thumbs" aria-label="Step 5 screenshots">
                <button type="button" class="step-thumb" data-full="/img/journal/Picture5.png" data-alt="Name notebook">
                  <img src="/img/journal/Picture5.png" alt="Name notebook thumbnail" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
                </button>
              </div>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ol>


          <!-- Mobile Steps -->
          <h3 class="bom-journal__subhead">Mobile Instructions - Click images to expand</h3>

          <ol class="setup-steps">
            <li class="setup-step">
              <span class="step-num">1</span>
